  <div class="container page-hero-grid">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
      <h1>
        Answers to the questions clients usually ask before they book, approve,
        or move a project forward.
      </h1>
      <p class="lead-copy">
        These answers are written to reduce uncertainty around scheduling,
        service fit, occupied-space work, and what typically affects scope.
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="page-hero-card">
      <h2>Fast answers</h2>
      <ul class="kicker-list">
        <li>Residential and light commercial work.</li>
        <li>Service areas across West Michigan.</li>
        <li>
          Booking is best for ready-to-schedule projects; contact is better for
          early planning.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="section-shell section-shell--contrast">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-lead">
      <span class="eyebrow">Common questions</span>
      <h2>What people usually want to know first.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-card">
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details open>
          <summary>What kinds of projects are the best fit?</summary>
          <p>
            Top Tier Electrical is strongest on panel upgrades, EV charger
            installations, lighting improvements, generator readiness,
            electrical repairs, remodel support, dedicated circuits, and premium
            residential or light commercial electrical work where finish quality
            matters.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>
            Do you work in occupied homes and active businesses?
          </summary>
          <p>
            Yes. A large part of the value is keeping the process orderly in
            lived-in homes, active offices, retail spaces, and other
            environments where mess, communication gaps, or poor coordination
            create unnecessary friction.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>
            How do I know whether to use the contact form or booking form?
          </summary>
          <p>
            Use the contact form when you want guidance, service-fit
            clarification, or early planning input. Use the booking form when
            you already know the project is moving forward and want to request
            scheduling.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>
            Do you handle both smaller fixes and larger upgrades?
          </summary>
          <p>
            Yes. The company handles focused repairs and corrections as well as
            broader upgrade scopes. The fit depends more on clarity, access, and
            project goals than on size alone.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What affects the final scope or price?</summary>
          <p>
            Access, panel condition, wiring path complexity, finish protection,
            equipment location, permit requirements, and coordination with other
            trades are common variables. The goal is to surface those factors
            early instead of letting them surprise the project later.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What areas do you serve?</summary>
          <p>
            Top Tier Electrical serves Holland, Grand Rapids, Allegan, Grand
            Haven, Muskegon, and surrounding West Michigan communities.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="section-shell">
